title: PPPP Mir Muhammad Sadiq Imrani wins PB-13 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peopleâ€™s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Mir Muhammad Sadiq Imrani has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-13, Naseerabad-I by securing 14,856 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner up was an Independent Candidate candidate Mir Sikandar Ali who bagged 9,505 votes.
Overall voters turn out remained 36.07 per cent.
